<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03136a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03136a">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03136a"> 136(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> all units of / brigade, keeping / touch for Brigadier</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[from an offical report about Mrs PC&apos;s son]</font>: and in one hour took position, and with officers and crews of tanks rounded up nearly 400 prisoners, including seven officers, after which, until relieved on November 15th at 4 P.M., acted as General Brigade liaison officer, <mark>keeping touch for Brigadier with all units of brigade</mark>. <small> Mrs Patrick Campbell, <a name="PCML" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#PCML"><cite title="source">My Life and Some Letters</cite></a> (1922) 385</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
